      <h1>H1 as title or heading —<br>what's actually correct?</h1>
      <p class="hero-lead">
        Markdown doesn't define what <code># H1</code> means semantically. The spec
        just says it's the largest heading. What it <em>represents</em> — document title,
        top-level section, or just "big text" — is left to convention. And conventions conflict.
      </p>
